 great so far. I did steps 1-4 yesterday in a couple of hours.<br /><br />10/25<br />1. Dawnshroud Peaks: I zoned in and there was an ooc about a shard rotting. Looted Shard<br />2. Scarlet Desert: There was a level 55 mage hunting shards when I zoned in. He said he had been there for hours. I asked if he was killing all the shard mobs. He said I could kill the ones in the back, since he couldn't kill them all. Result: 2 kills, Shard dropped!! I contemplated letting the poor mage loot the shard for about half a second, and then my greedy click button looted it for me.<br />3. Maiden's Eye: This took about 2 hours. I killed the 3 camps near AR. I did get adds occasionaly, but handled them without a problem. The roamers in this zone make it challenging.<br />4. The Grey: Yawn, 3 kills and shard dropped.<br /><br />I will start on number 5 today.<br /><br />10/26<br />5. Katta/Seru: I went to the Katta camp and killed 30 Centurions and no shard!!. So since I was fed up with that, I went to Seru. Got the Shard there on the walkway around the city in about 15 kills. Pet tanked and dotted.<br /><br />I went to Acrylia Caverns next (AR was camped). AC is a little more challenging to get to camp. I killed lots of bloodguards, but no shard yet. Also, beware: There are lots of casters here and it is hard to FD. Might be better to have Levant memmed instead of FD, but I haven't changed that out yet myself. Score: AC 1 Oliar 0 on this one. Will try again tomorrow.<br /><br />10/27<br />Akhevia Ruins: Follow the guide!! Got the Shard. But I didn't set off a trap.... hmmm.. oh well.<br /><br />Fungus Grove: Follow the guide!! Got the shard on 2nd round of killing.<br /><br />Acrylia Caverns: Got the shard today. Didn't Levant: Acrylia Caverns 1 Oliar 1 !!<br /><br />Went scouting the run in The Deep. I had sow. I used CoS and ran. I ran into some see invis mobs, but kept click CoS on to reduce other aggro. I used the ingame map and ran across the bridge with no problem where I Fd'ed. Just to be safe I /q'ed out. Killed a couple of Horrors, but I need to get to raid. Will update tomorrow.<br /><br />The Deep (I had time after all): My hp is higher than some, so getting buffs are ok. I did it self buffed. I did it with SoW, Circlet of Shadow, and the ingame map. Ran like hell, got aggro from see invis mob, kept clicking CoS, found invis bridge, used ingame map to walk across bridge(made it easy), got across and FD'ed.. /q'ed to make sure aggro gone. Turn left, follow ledge til you see Horrors. Kill and loot Shard. Took me about 5 kills.<br /><br />Time For SSRA!!!<br /><br />10/28<br />Got the SSRA shard!!... but /sigh not solo. Another guildmate needed shard, so I helped her and 2 dropped.<br /><br />Let me straighten out the guide on this. The camp is not the first camp on left where the torch is!!!! There are 3 skele's there. This is not the camp. Continue going and you will see another torch on the wall on your right hand side (go left and follow tunnel. Torch on right after seeing torch on left) There are 2 skeles at that torch. Follow the guide from there and you will be able to solo from that camp!!!<br /><br />OK. Tomorrow I will get the container in AR!!<br /><br />10/29: AR Container<br /><br />Do as the guide says and you'll be fine. Just a couple of points. <br /><br />1) I had to go up the stairs where the 3 4armeds are and then jump down to the remains platform.<br /><br />2) The South West remains is the one that aggros when you kill it. Only 1 mob aggroed and you can easily FD with Forceshield up.<br /><br /><br /> <br /><br />--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />Edited by - Oliar Corpsemaster on 10/30/2003 08:16:21 AM <br /><br />--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /> <br />Server: The Rathe | Posts: 100  <br /> <br />noodleor<br />Pile of Bones<br /><br /><br /> Posted - 10/29/2003 :  06:48:28 AM     <br />--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /> <br />9. I never had to do any qvox/hs jumping in the deep, just didn't go near the see-invis mobs. Then crossed the invisible bridge and took the first left in the thought horror tunnels then set up cmap before the tunnel curves right. Think I was there for about 2 hours and had 3 drop in that time. I was also using pet feign to split them up, tried a few times with darkness/fd but it only worked once and was a pain.<br /><br />3. I also charmed the sun revenants in the grey, WoT hardly ever breaks and with a hasted pet you spend most of the time waiting for re-pops. I got my shard on the 4th kill and since then have helped a few friends get thiers, took 3-4 clearings of the camp for those ones to drop.<br /><br />7. With the fungus grove shard once you've cleared the priest and 2 warriors at the back of the room (they're at the back if your facing the direction you entered from) you have plenty of room to kite them round. Took me 5 hours of killing to get my shard  but some friends got theirs a lot faster than that.<br /><br />5. I went to sanctus seru instead of katta for that shard and it sucked please don't spend 6 hours killing those stupid mobs and try katta first.<br /><br />Getting the sceptre was the hardest part I did solo, once you find the place just run to the altar and hope you channel fd. Pre-nerf CoS was extremely helpful here. If you look at the map in the first post the place your looking for is just to the right of the 'Perhaps Va`Dyn with PH spawns here', text. probably really close to where the 500 line crosses the -500 vertical line.<br /><br />I ended up grouping for the ssra shard and nothing new to add for any of the other ones.<br /><br /> <br /><br />--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /> <br />Server: Torvonnilous | Posts: 4  <br /> <br />Setsoru<br />Spectre<br /><br /><br /> Posted - 10/30/2003 :  4:06:12 PM         <br />--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /> <br />i did run into a see invis mob but i just fd and let him reset. first time i didn't hit him, but i fell off the bridge :\ so i went back & did the qvox trick. deep took me 2.5 hours or so<br /><br />i cleared sun revs just aggro kiting and was waiting a -long- time for repops, you dont have to charm less youre bored. wouldnt thrall of bones work as well? nothing but bad luck w/WoT here.<br /><br />bad luck on fg got mine in 30 min or so<br /><br />bad luck in seru, got mine in 40 min or so<br /><br />the guide pretty much will take care of it, i had a lot of problems in ahkeva pulling, none of the mobs would reset after fd even after 7 or 8 fd attempts. ps the rubble rousers have alot of hp :P<br /><br />AC can be a bitch if the high priest is wandering around, lvl 60 mobs, hits for 400+. i just played cute games with it till it ran oom, then root rotted it<br /> <br /> <br /></span></font></td>
