              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#3C4884" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2">Bonesmash</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#3C4884" valign="top"><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;12/17/2003&nbsp;: 10:13:54 AM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> I was able to complete all 10 in about 3 weeks of casual camping when nothing else was going on. I'll offer some tips: <br /><br />DSP, The Grey, and SD need no explination. <br /><br />Seru - I just killed all the guards in the catwalk that runs along the outside of the zone. I cleared all the guards once, then on the second clearing the shard dropped from An Intervallum Guard. <br /><br />ME - the infamous bottleneck shard. This shard is actually not that bad if you know what to kill. I was fortunate enough to have the zone to myself so I could claim all the shard camps. Take a look at this map:<br /><br /> <a href="http://bloodofro.com/user/samita/maiden4.jpg" target="_blank">http://bloodofro.com/user/samita/maiden4.jpg</a> <br /><br />The big black stars represent PHers, so there is no need to kill any of the other gorangas. <br /><br />Here's what I did as a necro: set up near the AR zone where it says "camp." Run to Battlemaster camp and split by rooting the non PH scout. Pull the PH to the camp and kill. Next, run to the prophet camp and root the scout NE of the PH. You can take the PH to you camp spot, or take him to the SE corner near the 3 scout spawn. Just don't get so close that you agro the 3 scouts there. <br /><br />Next, I would Succor myself to the DSP zoneline to clear agro and to put me close to the seer camp. Go to the Seer camp and target the Seer's PH, then target one of the other 2 scouts there. Now you can use Ctrl+Tab to cycle targets back and forth. This is improtant because on the pull you're gonna have 2 come, and you don't want to waste time by killing the wrong scout. Ok, now for the pull... use Ctrl+Tab to target the non PH scout and root him. Run back to the DSP zoneline and use Ctrl+Tab again to target the PH. Root him or snare him and FD split until you have the PH alone and kill him. (If you can't FD you can just root and zone to dsp. When you zone back in he'll be there waiting.) <br /><br />Now for the forager/savant camp. I only did this one about half the time because it takes a lot of time to do both of these and adds are almost guaranteed, but here's what to do. When the area is free from roamers, root the savant PH. Only the forager PH will follow you when you do this, so I would root savant, invis, and run to my camp spot by AR and kill him. Now the tricky part is the savant. Chances are root will have worn off by the time you kill the forager, so you can just invis and run toward him a little ways and he'll come darting after you. The problem here is that you have direct agro on the savant PH from rooting him, so whatever he passes by he's going to agro so there is potential for a massive train here. If you get a train, root the savant PH and zone to AR, come back and kill. <br /><br />That's the cycle for ME under perfect conditions. Chances are you're not going to be the only one there camping shards, so just apply the above strategy to whatever camps are available to you. <br /><br />FG - For this one run to the shik`nar caves near the TS zone in FG. You will see a big open room with a load of shik`nar foragers. In this room there is a cave that leads to the shik`nar nest (maps help). Go into the nest and make your first left. When you go into the next room there is only one other door, so go through it. In this room you'll see a bunch of baby beetles. This is the room you want because on the other side of the big rock in the middle of the room there are 4 warriors and a priest. The good thing about this camp is the shik`nar must be blind and deaf cuz their agro range is pathetic. There is a little clear spot near the tunnel you came in, that will be your pull spot. Start by killing the priest. I root dotted with no problems, so just kill however you are best suited. Once the priest is dead pull the closest warrior and just continue on around the room. I got singles every time, and you'll never get an add as long as you keep a little distance between the mob you are killing and the mobs that roam in the tunnel. <br /><br />AC - I found a lot of bad info on this one because of the AC revamp. You no longer need a key to access inner Acrylia. Follow any map to the inner acrylia portal and kill mobs there. The shard can drop off of any mob with "Sanctum" in it's name and it's a common drop. <br /><br />AR - I followed this guide from masters of the undead... <br /><br />Quote: <br />Akheva - shaded stones. Those are very annoying, because the chain agro like hell, zone in and invis then run straiht, then you come to an open room and keep running straight, and before you enter the next big room stop up because here there is a trap on the floor, so wakl very slowly and then you will get a message, it says something like yada yada is comming up from the floor. <br />Now you have to flee back to the zone and zone out, and you can do this with out letting the mobs hit on you. Zone back in and run back to the trap, and now the trap is releached so it wont spawn again, i think its respawns every 30 min. When you enter the big room look left, there is a lillte crack or place in the left corner where there is a mob. Root dot this mob, because this is gonna be you pull spot. It will respawn every 20 min. Until you have killed this mob watch out for roamers. Now you are ready to pull the Stones, but be carefull because they have a huge agro range, AND you will get more then 1 when you pull, bu after some FD`s you have the stone close to you without any agro from his friends. This is hard and it took me 8 kills before the shard dropped. And alot of deaths.  <br /><br /><br />I didn't have any deaths here and didn't see any problems. The shaded stones and shaded golems here don't hit hard and are easily root dotted. They are also easy to FD split. Just stay away from the rubble rousers  <br /><br />The Deep - This one was surprisingly easy, but I'm sure I had some luck going for me. Check out the map here: <br /><br /><a href="http://page.inf.fu-berlin.de/~fritsch/guide/pics/deep.jpg" target="_blank">http://page.inf.fu-berlin.de/~fritsch/guide/pics/deep.jpg</a> <br /><br />I was able to go to the invis bridge with invisible on only. There was one underbulk who saw invis, but he didn't agro so no biggie. If you have a cleric with you this is np, just pacify all the way down. Make sure you have maps installed and crossing the invis bridge is np. Follow the path to the pull area on the map and clear everything there. Shards are very common here. Usually 1-2 per clearing. I just let my pet tank and healed him to give you an idea of how easy the mobs are. <br /><br />Ssra - I can't take credit for soloing this one, cuz I got it on one of my SSra farming trips. They are way more common than green metal, so this one should be no problem.<br /><br />Well, that's all of them. <br /><br /><br />Oh, one more thing ...<br /> <br />The Deep <br />*************** <br />That map led me to believe I needed to go waaaay deeper than I needed to. Elder thought horrors..,,,,,suck. And see invis too. <br /><br />Anyways.... ripped this from Allakhazam..com.. <br /><br />********************** <br /><br />You need to cross the invisible bridge. There is a translucent bridge there that is false. You can't levitate in the zone and if you fall you take 20K. <br /><br />You can invis all the way to these, but careful as some mobs see invis on the way (only ones I found that see invis are the ones that wander, often you can wait for them to move away). <br />Once across the bridge turn left and pass the 'An Ancient Shrieker' area and you will see some 'A Horror Guard', 'A Thought Horror Evocer', and/or 'A Thought Horror Spiriter'. You should be able to single pull the first 5 at least, there are 2 more deeper in that I didn't try as the spawn rate is pretty fast. <br /><br />'A Horror Guard' has about 12K hps, doesn't cast spells - didn't resist any of my spells after a debuff took. <br /><br />'A Thought Horror Evocer' has 8-10K hps, is a Enchanter mob, casts spells, but easy to resist with resist magic on. Dispells and debuffs you so make sure you have junk buffs on to reduce the chance of losing hp or mana regen buffs. Will try to charm (Facination?) you. <br /><br />'A Thought Horror Spiriter' has 8-10K hps, is a Necromancer mob, casts spells, but easy to resist with resist magic on. Dispels and debuffs you so make sure you have junk buffs on to reduce the chance of losing hp or mana regen buffs. Will try to fear you. <br /><br />All 3 mobs are rootable, slowable and don't summon. <br />I talked with someone who got a shard after 15 or so kills, took me about 18 in all from these 3 mobs combined. <br /><br />One last thing there are thought leechs, those dont drop the shard, the horrors are the ones that do. Hope this info helps.<br />_________________ <br /> <br /></span></font></td>
              </tr>
